evidence.text: Plaintiffs filed suit against Defendants. The complaint asserts ultra vires, Tenth Amendment, and APA claims, all primarily based on the allegation that Defendants unlawfully called into federal service members of the California National Guard. The complaint seeks declaratory and injunctive relief.

On June 10, Plaintiffs moved for a TRO. Plaintiffs asserted that they were 'likely to suffer several types of irreparable harm in the absence of temporary relief,' highlighting as a 'stand[] out' harm 'the very high risk of substantial civil unrest as a direct result' of Defendants' deployment of the National Guard.
The district court granted the TRO that same day. ... Defendants immediately filed a notice of appeal and moved for an emergency stay pending appeal. ... We held oral argument on June 17, 2025.
